<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'>Hi,<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'>Is
there a way to detect a situation than one of the processes in an MPI
application exits without even calling MPI_Init()? <o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'>I
have a case in which all the processes except one are stuck forever in
MPI_Init(), and that one exits before being able to call MPI_Init()&#8230;<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'>I
tried using the mca params that I thought might be related -
orte_startup_timeout, orte_abort_timeout, but that didn&#8217;t help. <o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>

